# User Preferences & Context
- MacBook Pro 16" M5 Max, macOS Tahoe 26.5, zsh with p10k
- Custom llama wrapper at ~/.llama/ with modular files in llama.d/
- Prefers minimal/no redundant output; doesn't want informational fallback messages like "▶ Fallback: downloading..."
- Wants simple, direct tool behavior

# Project Conventions
- Internal shell functions prefixed with _llama_
- llama-aliases.sh is main entry point, sources modular llama.d/*.sh files
- Subcommands: run, serve, list, pull, rm, stop, ps, logs, doctor, config, bench, speed, pipe, convert, update-convert, check-convert, help
- llama convert auto-detects assistant/MTP vs full conversion
- llama pull offers conversion when no GGUF available in repo
- Models stored in ~/.llama/llama-models/
- Convert scripts in ~/.llama/convert/ (convert_hf_to_gguf.py, gguf-py/, conversion/, requirements.txt)

# Python Environment
- python3 at /usr/bin/python3, version 3.9.6 (macOS system Python)
- pip packages install to /Users/ergix/Library/Python/3.9/bin (not on PATH by default)
- Required: gguf, torch, transformers
- LibreSSL 2.8.3 compiled into Python; urllib3 v2 warning: "compiled with LibreSSL 2.8.3"

